# Push to GitHub (Vercel deploy)

After completing work in this project, commit and push to the `blackrock` remote unless the user explicitly says not to.

## Remote

- **Remote name:** `blackrock`
- **Repository:** https://github.com/owiekelvin3-cpu/Blackrock-reserve.git
- **Branch:** `main` (tracks `blackrock/main`)
- **Deploy:** Vercel auto-deploys from `main` → https://www.blackrockreserve.site

## Include

- Full app: marketing, auth, dashboard, **admin console**, API routes, components, libs, scripts
- Config: `package.json`, `next.config.mjs`, `prisma/`, docs, `.env.example`

## Exclude

- `.env` and any files with secrets or credentials
- `node_modules/`, `.next/`

## Workflow

1. Never `git add .env` or commit secrets.
2. Commit with a concise message focused on why.
3. Push: `git push blackrock main`
